 (72,'Lying Face Up Plate Neck Resistance','\n        <p>\n        </p><p></p><ol><li> Lie face up with your whole body straight on a flat bench while holding a weight plate on top of your forehead.  <strong>Tip:</strong> You will need to position yourself so that your shoulders are slightly above the end of a flat bench in order for the traps, neck and head to be off the bench.  This will be your starting position.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li> While keeping the plate secure on your forehead slowly lower your head back in a semi-circular motion as you breathe in.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li> Raise your head back up to the starting position in a semi-circular motion as you breathe out.  Hold the contraction for a second.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li> Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.</li>\r\n</ol><p><strong>Caution:</strong> As with all exercises, refrain from using any sort of sudden or jerking motions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Variation:</strong> You can opt to use no resistance at first.</p>\n    \n',1,89,90,1,2,51,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/lying-face-up-plate-neck-resistance',1,'8.1',4,13,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/26/Male/m/26_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/26/Male/m/26_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/26/Female/m/26_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/26/Female/m/26_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/6.gif'),
 (73,'Chin To Chest Stretch','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Get into a seated position on the floor.</li>\r\n<li> Place both hands at the rear of your head, fingers interlocked, thumbs pointing down and elbows pointing straight ahead. Slowly pull your head down to your chest. Hold for 20-30 seconds. </li>\r\n</ol>\n',1,1211,1212,0,2,67,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/chin-to-chest-stretch',3,'3.5',4,12,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/467/Male/m/467_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/467/Male/m/467_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/467/Female/m/467_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/467/Female/m/467_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/6.gif'),
 (74,'Neck-SMR','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Using a muscle roller or a rolling pin, place the roller behind your head and against your neck. Make sure that you do not place the roller directly against the spine, but turned slightly so that the roller is pressed against the muscles to either side of the spine. This will be your starting position.</li>\r\n<li> Starting at the top of your neck, slowly roll down the muscles of your neck, pausing at points of tension for 10-30 seconds. </li>\r\n</ol>\n',1,1213,1214,1,2,67,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/neck-smr',3,'2.3',4,13,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/628/Male/m/628_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/628/Male/m/628_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/628/Female/m/628_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/628/Female/m/628_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/6.gif'),
 (75,'Side Neck Stretch','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Start with your shoulders relaxed, gently tilt your head towards your shoulder.</li>\r\n<li> Assist stretch with a gentle pull on the side of the head.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',1,1215,1216,2,2,67,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/side-neck-stretch',1,'5.4',4,12,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/447/Male/m/447_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/447/Male/m/447_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/447/Female/m/447_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/447/Female/m/447_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/447/Female/m/447_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/447/Female/m/447_4.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/6.gif'),
