 (617,'One-Legged Cable Kickback','\n        <p>\n        </p><p></p><ol><li>Hook a leather ankle cuff to a low cable pulley and then attach the cuff to your ankle.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Face the weight stack from a distance of about two feet, grasping the steel frame for support.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>While keeping your knees and hips bent slightly and your abs tight, contract your glutes to slowly \"kick\" the working leg back in a semicircular arc as high as it will comfortably go as you breathe out. <strong>Tip:</strong> At full extension, squeeze your glutes for a second in order to achieve a peak contraction.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Now slowly bring your working leg forward, resisting the pull of the cable until you reach the starting position.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Switch legs and repeat the movement for the other side.</li>\r\n</ol><p><strong>Variations:</strong> You can perform this exercise with exercise bands.</p>\r\n\n    \n',0,939,940,110,2,62,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/one-legged-cable-kickback',1,'9.3',1,4,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/101/Male/m/101_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/101/Male/m/101_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/101/Female/m/101_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/101/Female/m/101_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/14.gif'),
 (618,'Pull Through','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Begin standing a few feet in front of a low pulley with a rope or handle attached. Face away from the machine, straddling the cable, with your feet set wide apart.</li>\r\n<li> Begin the movement by reaching through your legs as far as possible, bending at the hips. Keep your knees slightly bent. Keeping your arms straight, extend through the hip to stand straight up. Avoid pulling upward through the shoulders; all of the motion should originate through the hips. </li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,941,942,120,2,62,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/pull-through',2,'6.8',2,4,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/707/Male/m/707_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/707/Male/m/707_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/707/Female/m/707_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/707/Female/m/707_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/14.gif'),
 (619,'Single Leg Glute Bridge','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li> Lay on the floor with your feet flat and knees bent.</li>\r\n<li> Raise one leg off of the ground, pulling the knee to your chest. This will be your starting position.</li>\r\n<li> Execute the movement by driving through the heel, extending your hip upward and raising your glutes off of the ground.</li>\r\n<li> Extend as far as possible, pause and then return to the starting position.\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,943,944,130,2,62,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/single-leg-glute-bridge-',1,'9.0',4,3,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/915/Male/m/915_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/915/Male/m/915_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/915/Female/m/915_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/915/Female/m/915_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/14.gif'),
 (620,'Ankle On The Knee','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li> From a lying position, bend your knees and keep your feet on the floor. </li>\r\n<li> Place your ankle of one foot on your opposite knee.</li>\r\n<li>Grasp the thigh or knee of the bottom leg and pull both of your legs into the chest. Relax your neck and shoulders. Hold for 10-20 seconds and then switch sides.\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1347,1348,10,2,605,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/ankle-on-the-knee',3,'4.3',4,12,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/394/Male/m/394_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/394/Male/m/394_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/394/Female/m/394_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/394/Female/m/394_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/14.gif'),
 (621,'Knee Across The Body','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Lie down on the floor with your right leg straight. Bend your left leg and lower it across your body, holding the knee down toward the floor with your right hand. (The knee doesn\'t need to touch the floor if you\'re tight.)</li>\r\n<li> Place your left arm comfortably beside you and turn your head to the left. Imagine you have a weight tied to your tailbone. let your tailbone fall back toward the floor as your chest reaches in the opposite direction to stretch your lower back. Switch sides.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1349,1350,20,2,605,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/knee-across-the-body',3,'5.4',4,12,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/428/Male/m/428_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/428/Male/m/428_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/428/Female/m/428_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/428/Female/m/428_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/14.gif'),
 (622,'Lying Glute','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Lie on your back with your partner kneeling beside you.</li>\r\n<li> Flex the hip of one leg, raising it off of the floor. Rotate the leg so the foot is over the opposite hip, the lower leg perpendicular to your body. Your partner should hold the knee and ankle in place. This will be your starting position.</li>\r\n<li> Attempt to push your leg towards your partner, who should be preventing any actual movement of the leg.</li>\r\n<li> After 10-20 seconds, completely relax as your partner gently pushes the ankle and knee towards your chest. Be sure to inform your helper when the stretch is adequate to prevent injury or overstretching.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1351,1352,30,2,605,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/lying-glute',3,'6.3',4,3,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/605/Male/m/605_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/605/Male/m/605_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/605/Female/m/605_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/605/Female/m/605_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/14.gif'),
 (623,'One Knee To Chest','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Start off by lying on the floor. </li>\r\n<li> Extend one leg straight and pull the other knee to your chest. Hold under the knee joint to protect the kneecap.</li>\r\n<li> Gently tug that knee toward your nose. </li>\r\n<li>Switch sides. This stretches the buttocks and lower back of the bent leg and the hip flexor of the straight leg.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1353,1354,40,2,605,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/one-knee-to-chest',2,'3.8',4,12,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/401/Male/m/401_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/401/Male/m/401_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/401/Female/m/401_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/401/Female/m/401_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/14.gif'),
 (624,'Piriformis-SMR','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Sit with your buttocks on top of a foam roll. Bend your knees, and then cross one leg so that the ankle is over the knee. This will be your starting position.</li>\r\n<li> Shift your weight to the side of the crossed leg, rolling over the buttocks until you feel tension in your upper glute. You may assist the stretch by using one hand to pull the bent knee towards your chest. Hold this position for 10-30 seconds, and then switch sides.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1355,1356,50,2,605,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/piriformis-smr',1,'5.7',4,8,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/612/Male/m/612_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/612/Male/m/612_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/612/Female/m/612_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/612/Female/m/612_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/14.gif'),
 (625,'Seated Glute','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>In a seated position with your knees bent, cross one ankle over the opposite knee. Your partner will stand behind you. Now, lean forward as your partner braces your shoulders with their hands. This will be your starting position.</li>\r\n<li> Attempt to push your torso back for 10-20 seconds, as your partner prevents any actual movement of your torso.</li>\r\n<li> Now relax your muscles as your partner increases the stretch by gently pushing your torso forward for 10-20 seconds.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1357,1358,60,2,605,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/seated-glute',3,'0.0',4,3,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/620/Male/m/620_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/620/Male/m/620_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/620/Female/m/620_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/620/Female/m/620_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/14.gif'),
