 (774,'Ball Leg Curl','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Begin on the floor laying on your back with your feet on top of the ball.</li>\r\n<li> Position the ball so that when your legs are extended your ankles are on top of the ball. This will be your starting position.</li>\r\n<li>\r\n Raise your hips off of the ground, keeping your weight on the shoulder blades and your feet.</li>\r\n<li> Flex the knees, pulling the ball as close to you as you can, contracting the hamstrings.</li>\r\n<li> After a brief pause, return to the starting position.\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1093,1094,10,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/ball-leg-curl',1,'8.8',2,7,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/861/Male/m/861_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/861/Male/m/861_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/861/Female/m/861_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/861/Female/m/861_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (775,'Band Good Morning','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Using a 41 inch band, stand on one end, spreading your feet a small amount. Bend at the hips to loop the end of the band behind your neck. This will be your starting position. \r\n</li><li>Keeping your legs straight, extend through the hips to come to a near vertical position. </li>\r\n<li>Ensure that you do not round your back as you go down back to the starting position.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1095,1096,20,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/band-good-morning',2,'8.2',2,1,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/729/Male/m/729_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/729/Male/m/729_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/729/Female/m/729_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/729/Female/m/729_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (776,'Band Good Morning (Pull Through)','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Loop the band around a post. Standing a little ways away, loop the opposite end around the neck. Your hands can help hold the band in position.</li>\r\n<li> Begin by bending at the hips, getting your butt back as far as possible. Keep your back flat and bend forward to about 90 degrees. Your knees should be only slightly bent.</li>\r\n<li> Return to the starting position be driving through with the hips to come back to a standing position.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1097,1098,30,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/band-good-morning-pull-through',2,'8.3',2,1,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/740/Male/m/740_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/740/Male/m/740_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/740/Female/m/740_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/740/Female/m/740_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (777,'Clean','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>With a barbell on the floor close to the shins, take an overhand (or hook) grip just outside the legs. Lower your hips with the weight focused on the heels, back straight, head facing forward, chest up, with your shoulders just in front of the bar. This will be your starting position.</li><li>\r\n</li><li> Begin the first pull by driving through the heels, extending your knees. Your back angle should stay the same, and your arms should remain straight. Move the weight with control as you continue to above the knees.</li>\r\n<li> Next comes the second pull, the main source of acceleration for the clean. As the bar approaches the mid-thigh position, begin extending through the hips. In a jumping motion, accelerate by extending the hips, knees, and ankles, using speed to move the bar upward. There should be no need to actively pull through the arms to accelerate the weight; at the end of the second pull, the body should be fully extended, leaning slightly back, with the arms still extended. </li>\r\n<li> As full extension is achieved, transition into the third pull by aggressively shrugging and flexing the arms with the elbows up and out. At peak extension, aggressively pull yourself down, rotating your elbows under the bar as you do so. Receive the bar in a front squat position, the depth of which is dependent upon the height of the bar at the end of the third pull. The bar should be racked onto the protracted shoulders, lightly touching the throat with the hands relaxed. Continue to descend to the bottom squat position, which will help in the recovery.  </li>\r\n<li>Immediately recover by driving through the heels, keeping the torso upright and elbows up. Continue until you have risen to a standing position. </li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1099,1100,40,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/clean',2,'8.2',2,2,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/669/Male/m/669_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/669/Male/m/669_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/669/Male/m/669_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/669/Male/m/669_4.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/669/Female/m/669_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/669/Female/m/669_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/669/Female/m/669_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/669/Female/m/669_4.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (778,'Glute Ham Raise','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Begin by adjusting the equipment to fit your body. Place your feet against the footplate in between the rollers as you lie facedown. Your knees should be just behind the pad.</li>\r\n<li> Start from the bottom of the movement.  Keep your back arched as you begin the movement by flexing the knees. Drive your toes into the foot plate as you do so. Keep your upper body straight, and continue until your body is upright. </li>\r\n<li>Return to the starting position, keeping your descent under control.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1101,1102,50,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/glute-ham-raise',2,'9.4',4,10,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/685/Male/m/685_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/685/Male/m/685_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/685/Female/m/685_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/685/Female/m/685_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (779,'Good Morning','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Begin with a bar on a rack at shoulder height. Rack the bar across the rear of your shoulders as you would a power squat, not on top of your shoulders. Keep your back tight, shoulder blades pinched together, and your knees slightly bent. Step back from the rack.</li>\r\n<li> Begin by bending at the hips, moving them back as you bend over to near parallel. Keep your back arched and your cervical spine in proper alignment.</li>\r\n<li> Reverse the motion by extending through the hips with your glutes and hamstrings. Continue until you have returned to the starting position. </li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1103,1104,60,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/good-morning',2,'7.4',4,2,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/686/Male/m/686_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/686/Male/m/686_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/686/Female/m/686_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/686/Female/m/686_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (780,'Good Morning off Pins','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Begin with a bar on a rack at about the same height as your stomach. Bend over underneath the bar and rack the bar across the rear of your shoulders as you would a power squat, not on top of your shoulders. At the proper height, you should be near parallel to the floor when bent over.  Keep your back tight, shoulder blades pinched together, and your knees slightly bent.  Keep your back arched and your cervical spine in proper alignment. </li>\r\n<li>Begin the motion by extending through the hips with your glutes and hamstrings, and you are standing with the weight. Slowly lower the weight back to the pins returning to the starting position. </li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1105,1106,70,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/good-morning-off-pins',2,'0.0',4,2,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/687/Male/m/687_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/687/Male/m/687_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/687/Female/m/687_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/687/Female/m/687_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (781,'Hang Snatch','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Begin with a wide grip on the bar, with an overhand or hook grip. The feet should be directly below the hips with the feet turned out. Your knees should be slightly bent, and the torso inclined forward. The spine should be fully extended and the head facing forward. The bar should be at the hips. This will be your starting position.</li>\r\n<li> Aggressively extend through the legs and hips. At peak extension, shrug the shoulders and allow the elbows to flex to the side.</li>\r\n<li> As you move your feet into the receiving position, forcefully pull yourself below the bar as you elevate the bar overhead. Receive the bar with your body as low as possible and the arms fully extended overhead.</li>\r\n<li>Return to a standing position with the weight overhead. Follow by returning the weight to the ground under control.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1107,1108,80,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/hang-snatch',2,'9.0',2,2,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/690/Male/m/690_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/690/Male/m/690_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/690/Male/m/690_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/690/Male/m/690_4.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/690/Female/m/690_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/690/Female/m/690_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/690/Female/m/690_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/690/Female/m/690_4.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (782,'Hang Snatch - Below Knees','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Begin with a wide grip on the bar, with an overhand or hook grip. The feet should be directly below the hips with the feet turned out. Your knees should be slightly bent, and the torso inclined forward. The spine should be fully extended and the head facing forward. The bar should be just below the knees. This will be your starting position.</li>\r\n<li> Aggressively extend through the legs and hips. At peak extension, shrug the shoulders and allow the elbows to flex to the side.</li>\r\n<li> As you move your feet into the receiving position, forcefully pull yourself below the bar as you elevate the bar overhead. Receive the bar with your body as low as possible and the arms fully extended overhead.</li>\r\n<li>Return to a standing position with the weight overhead, and then return the weight to the floor under control.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1109,1110,90,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/hang-snatch-below-knees',2,'0.0',2,2,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/691/Male/m/691_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/691/Male/m/691_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/691/Male/m/691_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/691/Male/m/691_4.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/691/Female/m/691_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/691/Female/m/691_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/691/Female/m/691_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/691/Female/m/691_4.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (783,'Hanging Bar Good Morning','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Begin with a bar on a rack at about the same height as your stomach. Suspend the bar using chains or suspension straps.</li>\r\n<li> Bend over underneath the bar and rack the bar across the rear of your shoulders as you would a power squat, not on top of your traps. At the proper height, you should be near parallel to the floor when bent over.  Keep your back tight, shoulder blades pinched together, and your knees slightly bent.  Keep your back arched and your cervical spine in proper alignment.</li>\r\n<li> Begin the motion by extending through the hips with your glutes and hamstrings, and you are standing with the weight.</li>\r\n<li> Slowly lower the weight back to the starting position, where it is supported by the chains. </li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1111,1112,100,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/hanging-bar-good-morning',2,'0.0',4,2,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/692/Male/m/692_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/692/Male/m/692_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/692/Female/m/692_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/692/Female/m/692_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (784,'Kettlebell Dead Clean','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Place kettlebell between your feet. To get in the starting position, push your butt back and look straight ahead.</li>\r\n<li> Clean the kettlebell to your shoulder.  Clean the kettlebell to your shoulders by extending through the legs and hips as you raise the kettlebell towards your shoulder. The wrist should rotate as you do so. </li>\r\n<li> Lower the kettlebell, keeping the hamstrings loaded by keeping your back straight and your butt out.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1113,1114,110,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/kettlebell-dead-clean',2,'0.0',4,9,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/549/Male/m/549_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/549/Male/m/549_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/549/Female/m/549_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/549/Female/m/549_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (785,'Kettlebell Hang Clean','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Place kettlebell between your feet. To get in the starting position, push your butt back and look straight ahead.</li>\r\n<li> Clean kettlebell to your shoulder. Clean the kettlebell to your shoulders by extending through the legs and hips as you raise the kettlebell towards your shoulder. The wrist should rotate as you do so.</li>\r\n<li> Lower kettlebell to a hanging position between your legs while keeping the hamstrings loaded. Keep your head up at all times.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1115,1116,120,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/kettlebell-hang-clean',2,'0.0',4,9,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/551/Male/m/551_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/551/Male/m/551_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/551/Male/m/551_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/551/Female/m/551_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/551/Female/m/551_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (786,'Kettlebell One-Legged Deadlift','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Hold a kettlebell by the handle in one hand. Stand on one leg, on the same side that you hold the kettlebell.</li>\r\n<li> Keeping that knee slightly bent, perform a stiff legged deadlift by bending at the hip, extending your free leg behind you for balance. </li>\r\n<li>\r\nContinue lowering the kettlebell until you are parallel to the ground, and then return to the upright position.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1117,1118,130,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/kettlebell-one-legged-deadlift',2,'9.4',4,9,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/546/Male/m/546_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/546/Male/m/546_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/546/Female/m/546_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/546/Female/m/546_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (787,'Lying Leg Curls','\n        <p>\n        </p><p></p><ol><li>Adjust the machine lever to fit your height and lie face down on the leg curl machine with the pad of the lever on the back of your legs (just a few inches under the calves).  <strong>Tip:</strong> Preferably use a leg curl machine that is angled as opposed to flat since an angled position is more favorable for hamstrings recruitment.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Keeping the torso flat on the bench, ensure your legs are fully stretched and grab the side handles of the machine.  Position your toes straight (or you can also use any of the other two stances described on the foot positioning section).  This will be your starting position.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>As you exhale, curl your legs up as far as possible without lifting the upper legs from the pad.  Once you hit the fully contracted position, hold it for a second.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>As you inhale, bring the legs back to the initial position.  Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.</li>\r\n</ol><p><strong>Caution:</strong> Do not ever use so much weight on the exercise that you start using swinging and jerking as you can risk both lower back injury and also a hamstring injury.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Variations:</strong> Since you have three foot positions you have in reality three exercises.  The movement can also be performed with a dumbbell held in between your feet (a partner needs to place it properly).  This latter exercise though is only suitable for advanced trainees.  Finally, it is also possible to just use one leg at a time for better isolation.</p>\r\n\n    \n',0,1119,1120,140,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/lying-leg-curls',1,'8.8',2,10,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/52/Male/m/52_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/52/Male/m/52_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/52/Female/m/52_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/52/Female/m/52_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (788,'Muscle Snatch','\n        <p>\n         </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Begin with a loaded barbell held at the mid thigh position with a wide grip.  The feet should be directly below the hips, with the feet turned out as needed. Lower the hips, with the chest up and the head looking forward. The shoulders should be just in front of the bar. This will be the starting position.</li>\r\n<li> Begin the pull by driving through the front of the heels, raising the bar. Transition into the second pull by extending through the hips knees and ankles, driving the bar up as quickly as possible. The bar should be close to the body. </li>\r\n<li>Continue raising the bar to the overhead position, without rebending the knees.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1121,1122,150,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/muscle-snatch',2,'0.0',4,2,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/699/Male/m/699_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/699/Male/m/699_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/699/Male/m/699_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/699/Female/m/699_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/699/Female/m/699_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/699/Female/m/699_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/699/Female/m/699_4.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (789,'One-Arm Kettlebell Clean','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Place a kettlebell between your feet. As you bend down to grab the kettlebell, push your butt back and keep your eyes looking forward.</li>\r\n<li> Clean the kettlebell to your shoulders by extending through the legs and hips as you raise the kettlebell towards your shoulder. The wrist should rotate as you do so.</li>\r\n<li> Return the weight to the starting position.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1123,1124,160,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/one-arm-kettlebell-clean',2,'0.0',4,9,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/513/Male/m/513_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/513/Male/m/513_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/513/Male/m/513_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/513/Female/m/513_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/513/Female/m/513_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/513/Female/m/513_3.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (790,'One-Arm Kettlebell Swings','\n        <p>\n        Place one kettlebell between your feet. Push back with your butt and bend your knees to get into the starting position. Make sure that your back is\r\nflat and look straight ahead. Swing the kettlebell between your legs forcefully. Quickly reverse the direction and drive though with your hips\r\ntaking the kettlebell straight out. Let the kettlebell swing back between your legs and repeat. Switch arms with each set.\r\n</p><font size=\"1\">Pictures And Videos Courtesy Of  <a href=\"http://www.artofstrength.com\" target=\"_blank\">artofstrength.com</a>.</font>\n    \n',0,1125,1126,170,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/one-arm-kettlebell-swings',2,'0.0',4,9,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/518/Male/m/518_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/518/Male/m/518_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/518/Male/m/518_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/518/Female/m/518_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/518/Female/m/518_2.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (791,'One-Arm Open Palm Kettlebell Clean','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Place one kettlebell between your feet.</li>\r\n<li> Grab the handle with one hand and raise the kettlebell rapidly, let it flip so that the ball of the kettlebell lands in the palm of\r\nyour hand.</li>\r\n<li> Throw the kettlebell out in front of you and catch the handle with one hand.</li>\r\n<li> Take the kettlebell to the floor and repeat.  Make sure to work both arms.</li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1127,1128,180,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/one-arm-open-palm-kettlebell-clean-',2,'0.0',4,9,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/541/Male/m/541_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/541/Male/m/541_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/541/Male/m/541_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/541/Female/m/541_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/541/Female/m/541_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/541/Female/m/541_3.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif'),
 (792,'Open Palm Kettlebell Clean','\n        <p>\n        </p><p>\r\n</p><ol><li>Place one kettlebell between your feet. Clean the kettlebell by extending through the legs and hips as you raise the kettlebell towards your shoulders.</li>\r\n<li> Release the kettlebell as it comes up, and let it flip so that the ball of the kettlebell lands in the palms of your hands.</li>\r\n<li> Release the kettlebell out in front of you and catch the handle with both hands. Lower the kettlebell to the starting position and repeat. </li>\r\n</ol>\n',0,1129,1130,190,2,64,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/detail/view/name/open-palm-kettlebell-clean-',2,'0.0',2,9,'http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/539/Male/m/539_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/539/Male/m/539_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/539/Male/m/539_3.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/539/Female/m/539_1.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/539/Female/m/539_2.jpg,http://www.bodybuilding.com/exercises/exerciseImages/sequences/539/Female/m/539_3.jpg','http://assets.bodybuilding.com/images/trackers/exercise/heatmap/8.gif');
